{
  "analysis": "The image is a raw 256MB disk with a DOS/MBR boot sector and FAT16 partition - a bootable Windows 3.11 installation. QEMU 8.2.2 is installed (newer than 5.2.0 but should work). Now I need to launch QEMU with all required options and set up the web interface.",
  "plan": "1. Launch QEMU in background with: snapshot mode, VNC :1, monitor socket, appropriate machine settings for Win3.11 (low RAM, i386 CPU). 2. Start websockify to bridge VNC to websocket. 3. Configure nginx to proxy port 80 to websockify. 4. Wait for VM to boot to desktop.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 \\\n  -m 32 \\\n  -cpu 486 \\\n  -hda /app/isos/win311.img \\\n  -snapshot \\\n  -vnc :1 \\\n  -monitor unix:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock,server,nowait \\\n  -device VGA \\\n  -netdev user,id=net0 \\\n  -device ne2k_isa,netdev=net0 \\\n  -boot c \\\n  -display none \\\n  > /tmp/qemu.log 2>&1 &\n",
